b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Lingvanex is best suited for privacy conscious organizations, on premise needs, mobile apps, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Smartling, meanwhile, shines for enterprise localization, SaaS companies, global brands, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2018, Lingvanex describes itself as \"Machine translation platform with cloud, on-premise, and mobile deployment options.\" Smartling, established in 2009, positions itself as \"Enterprise translation management platform combining AI and human translation.\" With 9 years between them, Smartling brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Lingvanex offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Smartling** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 5.0), more features (9 vs 4). However, this does not mean Lingvanex is a poor choice — far from it. Lingvanex excels in its own right, particularly for privacy conscious organizations and on premise needs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent enterprise tms platform, go with Smartling. If on-premise deployment option matters more to you, Lingvanex is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
